comment: Hawes (LAC) and Davis (LAC) set a double screen on Batum (POR) and give him the opportunity to stop and/or change directions.
Paul (LAC) loses control of his dribble and turns the ball over.
Jordan (LAC) sets a screen on Matthews (POR) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the ball be awarded to LAC was upheld.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the game clock was adjusted to 00:02.8 and the shot clock was adjusted to 00:01.7.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that a clock malfunction occurred was upheld. Regulation time was determined to be over.
Paul (LAC) makes contact with Aldridge's (POR) arm. The contact occurs before the start of his upward shooting motion and is therefore deemed a personal foul.
Turkoglu (LAC) splits his feet on the perimeter.
Turkoglu (LAC) makes contact with Batum (POR) in transition and affects his RSBQ.
Rivers (LAC) fouls Batum (POR) while he is in the air attempting the layup.
Redick's (LAC) contact with the off arm of Lillard (POR) as he catches the alley-oop does not affect his ability to finish the layup.
While not conclusive, RATR angle appears to show that Jordan (LAC) touches the ball while it was still in the cylinder.
Jordan (LAC) contests shot by Aldridge (POR), making "high-five" contact with his hand after the release of the shot, which is legal.
Redick (LAC) makes contact with Matthews' (POR) arm, affecting his ability to control the ball.
Batum (POR) cleanly blocks the layup attempt by Redick (LAC).
Batum (POR) grabs Jordan's (LAC) jersey during the rebound attempt.
Matthews (POR) dislodges Rivers (LAC) while chasing down the loose ball.
Rivers (LAC) grabs the shoulder of Lillard (POR) as he dribbles out the clock. Take foul should have been called.
